'You there, [placeholder], I have task for you.

'Chieftains command great numbers of the Enemy's forces, second only to the tyrants that lead the war-host.

'Should you run afoul of these terrors, slay them and bring me their seals so that I might see you rewarded for their defeat.'

'Each Chieftain that falls strengthens our position, [placeholder]. You are a hero to all the Free Peoples. Seek Quartermaster Ash at Gl√¢n Vraig to earn greater recognition of your efforts in the Ettenmoors.'
'Five Chieftain's seals will earn you a Token of Valour, [placeholder]. Keep hunting the Enemy.'
First Marshal Sathryth at Ost Ringdyr is collecting seals found on the Chieftains of Angmar's army in the Ettenmoors.
Return Chieftain's seals to First Marshal Sathryth

The Chieftains of Angmar may be found among the Enemy in the Ettenmoors.\n\nChieftains amongst Angmar's army bear seals that denote their station. Slay them and take their seals to earn recognition amongst the Free Peoples. First Marshal Sathryth has promised a reward for the seals you bring her.
